raw_data.title: Cloud Sr. Architect
raw_data.description: Provides expertise on the future state hosting solutions and perform work to achieve organization objectives. Serves as liaison between the various technical disciplines to ensure an overall integrated solution for cloud computing, including the development of a current state to future state assessment and roadmap. Works independently or with operations staff members to conduct Application Rationalization and Application Transformation objectives for cloud migration and modernization actitivies. Provides architecture, engineering, and integration expertise. Develops clodu disaster recovery methodologies and plans.

raw_data.title: Cloud Sr. Systems Engineer
raw_data.description: Installs and configures enterprise software packages in a cloud environment. Conducts engineering efforts that support and maintain enterprise system functions, including providing the necessary advice, assistance, planning and technical expertise to ensure integration, interoperability, and standards compliance. Perform technical planning, system integration, verification and validation, cost and risk, and supportability and effectiveness analyses for total cloud systems.

raw_data.title: Cloud Sr. Application Release Manager
raw_data.description: Supports the relationship between cloud operations and business teams. Coordinates application deployment, environment patching, and resource consumption in a cloud environment. Coordinates planned and unplanned maintenance including incidence response and recovery events. Document application architectural changes based on identified business requirements. Provide support and guidance throughout the process lifecycle.
raw_data.key_words: cloud application release,release management,cloud release management

raw_data.title: Principal Software/Systems Engineer
raw_data.description: Designs, develops, troubleshoots, and analyzes software programs for for enterprise implementation.  Conduct requirement analysis, system design, and simulations.  Develops or makes enhancements to existing systems to meet business requirements and technical roadmaps.  Includes architecture planning, technology analysis & comparisons, test planning, and system testing.  Areas of expertise include Java, Microsoft, Agile development, DevOps, Service Oriented Architecture, application database design, and networking.  Provides daily supervision and directions to staff.

raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: Program managers are experienced software and systems engineering managers and business division leaders who are experts in strategic analysis, management consulting, enterprise process modeling and leading multiple development teams.  Provides team leadership and creativity in the development and implementation of services engagements. Directs multiple and complex projects or sub-projects, including project financials. Manages and leads large work teams. Sets objectives and priorities for the project staff. Assigns and reviews tasks, performance, and staffing requirements. Identifies and pursues new business opportunities within the existing client bases.

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Project Managers Staff personnel are experienced systems and software engineering managers who are capable of leading a team through all phases of the software development cycle.  Manages projects of moderate risk and complexity. Oversees program/project budget and schedules. May have primary responsibility for program/project growth. Serves as primary customer contact.

raw_data.title: Quality Assurance Specialist
raw_data.description: Ensures that quality software is provided for release to production by independently executing test scripts.  Provide the means and also the measures for testing all the aspects of a software solution, both functionally and technically, in order to meet the requirements and overall quality of the intended solution.

raw_data.title: Sr. Architect
raw_data.description: Responsible for working with key stakeholders to understand the requirements for an IT system, articulating and communicating the vision for the IT architecture, and  providing leadership to the IT architecture and application teams.  Support the analysis and creation of a enterprise IT strategy and roadmap.  Assists client staff by working on IT studies, modeling system and/or sub-systems.  Conduct IT market research to access commercial IT tools and solutions.  Supports Project Management to resolve any IT technical issues or problems, if necessary.   Supervise teams and may provide not only technical, but functional experience as well.

raw_data.title: Sr. Database Administrator
raw_data.description: Provides expertise and guidance in the use of database management systems.  Provides technical consulting in the definition, design, and creation of a database environment.  Identifies database requirements by interviewing customers; analyzing department applications, programming, and operations; evaluating existing systems and designing proposed systems.  Implements and maintains databases, standards, controls, procedures, and documentation.  Maintains database dictionaries and documents JCL, shell scripts and batch processes. Ensures that documentation is complete and up-to-date. Develops and applies procedures for periodic database backup.

raw_data.title: Sr. DevOps Engineer
raw_data.description: Responsible for researching, designing, and implementing configuration management, continuous integration, and continuous delivery solutions.  Review and amend process workflows so that automated approaches can be implemented, while complying with client requirement for items such as security and version control.  Provide daily supervision and directions to staff.  Mentors others in the adoption of DevOps principles.

raw_data.title: Sr. Supply Chain Analyst
raw_data.description: Gathers data and conducts analysis with the goal of improving the organization's supply chain operations. Identifies underperforming areas in the supply chain and may suggest improvements or resolutions to problems. May assist in the negotiation of supplier contracts or service arrangements. Conducts financial analysis, inventory management, and contract analysis support. Uses analytical and quantitative methods to understand, predict, and enhance supply chain processes.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert I
raw_data.description: Subject matter experts are recognized by their peers through certifications and awards as leading experts in the fields of computer software design and implementation, business re-engineering, enterprise modeling, strategic planning, business planning and systems architecture plans.  High level of knowledge of client needs for special projects. May possess certifications in a specific technical or management discipline. Develops specifications for moderately complex applications and business information systems.

raw_data.description: Communications & writing personnel provides writing assistance in support of the development of client documentation such as Process Guides, reference materials, User Guides, Concept of Operations and other project related documentation.

raw_data.title: Sr. Supply Chain Analyst - Off-site

Identifies underperforming areas in the vendor supply chain and may suggest improvements or resolutions to problems. May assist in the negotiation of supplier contracts or service arrangements. Conducts financial analysis, inventory management, and contract analysis support. Uses analytical and quantitative methods to understand, predict, and enhance supply chain processes.
